resource.name: Vicarious Trauma Toolkit Compendium of Resources
State PREA Reports
resource.description:
This dataset lists every confinement facility identified by the nation’s state and territorial governors that is under their operational control, and is designed so that visitors can determine if and when during each three year PREA Audit Cycle a given facility was audited. Visitors to this site can link directly to final PREA audit reports for facilities that are under governors’ operational control and have received a PREA audit. PREA Standards 115.401(a) and 115.401(b) require agencies to audit all facilities at least once every three years, and to audit one-third of each facility type covered by the Standards (prisons and jails, community confinement facilities, lockups, and juvenile facilities) every year.

For more information about PREA and the contents on this website, please see these FAQs (https://bja.ojp.gov/sites/g/files/xyckuh186/files/media/document/JFARA%20Website_FAQs_FINAL_101617_508.pdf).

resource.name: OVC and BJA Funded Human Trafficking Services and Task Forces
resource.description:
OVC began funding trafficking victim service providers under the Services for Victims of Human Trafficking Program area in 2003. In 2010, OVC and the Bureau of Justice Assistance (BJA) began funding Enhanced Collaborative Model Task Force sites.

The interactive U.S. map below shows the breadth of victim services and support coverage provided by OVC grantees and the OVC and BJA-funded human trafficking task forces. 

The map contains links to task forces and victim services websites that are external to the OVC website. OVC provides these links as a convenience to its users and should not be construed as an endorsement by OVC. Read the website links disclaimer (https://www.ovc.gov/disclaimer.html).

*Comprehensive Services are provided either in-house or through project partners. The services include but are not limited to:

- Intake and eligibility assessment
- Intensive case management
- Shelter/housing and sustenance
- Medical care and substance abuse treatment
- Dental care
- Mental health treatment
- Individual counseling, group counseling
- Interpreter/translator services
- Legal immigration services
- Assistance in achieving HHS certification as a victim of human trafficking
- Legal assistance on family and civil matters
- Victim advocacy
- Literacy education and education
- Transportation assistance
- Life skills training
- 24-hour evening and weekend response to client emergencies
resource.attribution: Office of Justice Programs (OJP)/Office for Victims of Crime (OVC)
